fr.xephi.authme.command

Class CommandDescription

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.xephi.authme.command.CommandDescription

  • public class CommandDescription
extends Object
    Command description â€“ defines which labels ("names") will lead to a command and points to the ExecutableCommand implementation that executes the logic of the command.

    CommandDescription instances are built hierarchically: they have one parent, or null for base commands (main commands such as /authme), and may have multiple children extending the mapping of the parent: e.g. if /authme has a child whose label is "register", then /authme register is the command that the child defines.

    • Method Detail

      • getLabels

        public List<String> getLabels()
        Return all relative labels of this command. For example, if this object describes /authme register and /authme r, then it will return a list with register and r. The parent label authme is not returned.
        Returns:
        All labels of the command description.

      • hasLabel

        public boolean hasLabel(String commandLabel)
        Check whether this command description has the given label.
        Parameters:
        commandLabel - The label to check for.
        Returns:
        true if this command contains the given label, false otherwise.

      • getLabelCount

        public int getLabelCount()
        Return the number of labels necessary to get to this command. This corresponds to the number of parents + 1.
        Returns:
        The number of labels, e.g. for "/authme abc def" the label count is 3
